==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trillion
<hw>Tril"lion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>trillion</ets>, formed from the pref. <ets>tri-</ets> in imitation
of <ets>million</ets> a million. Cf. <er>Billion</er>.]</ety>
<def>According to the French notation, which is used upon the Continent
generally and in the United States, the number expressed by a unit with
twelve ciphers annexed; a million millions; according to the English
notation, the number produced by involving a million to the third power,
or the number represented by a unit with eighteen ciphers annexed. See
the Note under <er>Numeration</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trillium</ent>⟦br⟧
